x4freetext: The 9Be targets were produced by evaporating 9Be
metal onto platinum blanks the uniformity of the
The Li targets were made by evaporating pure Li metal
Of LiF onto platinum blanks. The thickness of the LiF
targets were determined by weighting before and after
The 13C targets were made by cracking methyl iodide,
enriched to about 60% in 13C, onto heated platium
blanks. The thickness of the 13C targets are not known
The absolute cross sections reported in
this paper may be in error as much as 50% while
relative values are good to within 7%. The principal
uncertainty is the approximations that were made in
solving the plastic scintillator efficiency integrals.
CNPD: corrected 4-dig. year and lower cases.
